etymologies: mid 16th century (in tertiary (sense 2 of the noun)): from Latin tertiarius ‘of the third part or rank’, from tertius ‘third’

examples.text: the tertiary stage of the disease
most of the enterprises were of tertiary importance

definitions: relating to or denoting education at a level beyond that provided by schools, especially that provided by a college or university.
shortDefinitions: of education at level beyond that provided by schools

definitions: relating to or denoting the medical treatment provided at a specialist institution
shortDefinitions: of medical treatment provided at specialist institution

definitions: relating to or denoting the first period of the Cenozoic era, between the Cretaceous and Quaternary periods, and comprising the Paleogene and Neogene subperiods.
shortDefinitions: of first period of Cenozoic era, between Cretaceous and Quaternary periods

definitions: (of an organic compound) having its functional group located on a carbon atom which is itself bonded to three other carbon atoms.
shortDefinitions: (of organic compound) having its functional group located on carbon atom which is itself bonded to three other carbon atoms

definitions: (chiefly of amines) derived from ammonia by replacement of three hydrogen atoms by organic groups.
shortDefinitions: (chiefly of amines) derived from ammonia by replacement of three hydrogen atoms by organic groups

definitions: denoting or relating to carnivores that eat other carnivores and omnivores

examples.text: the tertiary consumers must hunt for their food

shortDefinitions: denoting carnivores that eat other carnivores and omnivores

definitions: the Tertiary period or the system of rocks deposited during it.

notes.text: The Tertiary lasted from about 65 million to 1.6 million years ago. The mammals diversified following the demise of the dinosaurs and became dominant, as did the flowering plants

shortDefinitions: Tertiary period or system of rocks deposited during it

definitions: a lay associate of certain Christian monastic organizations
shortDefinitions: lay associate of certain Christian monastic organizations
